Millennium Demo Queries¶

In this notebook we show how the demo queries from http://gavo.mpa-garching.mpg.de/Millennium translate to the SciServer/CasJobs interface.

Schema documentation¶

The databases of the Millennium database can be accessed by joining the "Cosmology" science domain in SciServer.
TBD document how
Once when has joined this domain, in CasJobs one can find some 15 new databases beoyond the public SDSS databases. For example in the Query page "context' drop downm one now see databases like MPAHaloTrees, millimil, Guo2010a etc.
(Note, one may need to refresh the CasJobs web page after joining the science domain).

The contents of these databases is documented at the 'Schema Browser' tab. For most (but not yet all) tables once can listthe columns with their name, datatype, unit and description.
For a more comprehensive (though not more complete) documentation we refer to the original pages at http://gavo.mpa-garching.mpg.de/Millennium/Help/publicdbs.

H3¶

Find the progenitors at a given redshift (snapnum) of all halos of mass(np)≥4000 at a later redshift (snapnum). The progenitors are limited in mass as well.

In [44]:
sql="""
select DES.haloId as descendant_id,
       DES.np as descendant_mass,
       PROG.haloid,prog.x,prog.y,prog.z,prog.np
  from millimil..MPAHalo DES,
       millimil..MPAHalo PROG
 where DES.snapnum = 63
   and DES.np > 10000
   and PROG.haloId between DES.haloId and DES.lastprogenitorId
   and PROG.snapnum = 40
   and PROG.np > 100
 order by DES.np desc, PROG.np desc
"""
df=cj.executeQuery(sql,"millimil")
print(len(df),"halos")
df.head()

H4¶

Find all the halos of mass ≥ 1000 that have just had a major merger, defined by having at least two progenitors of mass ≥ 0.2*descendant mass.

In [47]:
sql="""
select D.haloId,
       D.snapnum,
       D.np as d_np,
       p1.haloid as p1_id,
       P1.np as p1_np,
       p2.haloid as p2_id,
       P2.np as p2_np
  from millimil..MPAHalo P1,
       millimil..MPAHalo P2,
       millimil..MPAHalo D
 where P1.SNAPNUM=P2.SNAPNUM
   and P1.haloId < P2.haloId
   and P1.descendantId = D.haloId
   and P2.descendantId = D.haloId
   and P1.np >= .2*D.np
   and P2.np >= .2*D.np
   and D.np > 1000
"""
df=cj.executeQuery(sql,"millimil")
print(len(df),"major mergers")
df.head()

39 major mergers

NB it is important to note that the mass of a satellite subhalo generally reduces for some time before it merges with the central halo. Hence the mass at thsnapshot just before merging is generally not an accurate representation of its original mass. This affects the definition of what constitutes a major merger.

HF2¶

Find halo mass functions in overdensities at two different values.

In [53]:
sql="""
   select '3 - 5' as lim, 
       power(10, .1*(.5+floor(log10(h.np)/.1))) as mass,
       count(*) as num
  from millimil..MPAHalo h, 
       millimil..MMField f
 where f.g5 between 3 and 5
   and f.snapnum=63
   and f.snapnum = h.snapnum
   and f.phkey = h.phkey    
 group by 0*haloId, power(10, .1*(.5+floor(log10(h.np)/.1)))
union
 select '0.2 - 0.4' as lim,
        power(10, .1*(.5+floor(log10(h.np)/.1))) as mass,
        count(*) as num
  from millimil..MPAHalo h, 
       millimil..MMField f
 where f.g5 between .2 and .4
   and f.snapnum=63
   and f.snapnum = h.snapnum
   and f.phkey = h.phkey    
 group by 0*haloId+1, power(10, .1*(.5+floor(log10(h.np)/.1)))
order by lim,mass    

"""
mfs=cj.executeQuery(sql,"millimil")
In [54]:
groups=mfs.groupby(['lim'])
f,(ax)=plt.subplots(1,1,figsize=(8,5))
for i,group in groups:
    ax.plot(group.mass,group.num,'-o',label=i)
ax.set_xscale('log')
ax.set_yscale('log');
ax.legend();

HF3¶

Assembly Bias ala Gao & White (2007).
Find formation time dependency on background overdensities for halos in particular mass bin.

In [55]:
sql="""
select zmax, avg(g5) as g5, stdev(g5) as g5err,
       avg(g10) as g10, stdev(g10) as g10err,
       count(*) as num
  from millimil..mmfield f, 
       ( select des.haloId, des.np, des.phkey,max(PROG.redshift) as zmax
           from millimil..MPAHalo PROG,
                millimil..MPAHalo DES
          where DES.snapnum = 63
            and PROG.haloId between DES.haloId and DES.lastprogenitorId
            and prog.np >= des.np/2    
            and des.np between 100 and 200
            and des.haloId = des.firsthaloinfofgroupid
          group by des.haloId, des.np ,des.phkey    
       ) t
 where t.phkey = f.phkey 
   and f.snapnum=63
group by zmax 
"""
time_form=cj.executeQuery(sql,"millimil")
In [56]:
plt.plot(time_form.g10,time_form.zmax,'-o')
plt.xlabel('overdensity 10 Mpc')
plt.ylabel('$z_{form}$');

sql="""
select DES.galaxyId as descendant_id,
       DES.stellarMass as descendant_mass,
       PROG.*
  from millimil..DeLucia2006a DES,
       millimil..DeLucia2006a PROG
 where DES.snapnum = 63
   and DES.mag_b < -20
   and PROG.galaxyId between DES.galaxyId and DES.lastprogenitorId
   and PROG.snapnum = 30
   and PROG.mag_b < -19
 order by DES.mag_b asc, PROG.mag_b asc
"""

HG1¶

Find the conditional luminosity functions for galaxies in two ranges of halo masses

In [108]:
sql="""
select '2000 - 3000' as lim, 
       .2*(.5+floor(mag_b/.2)) as mag,
       count(*) as num
  from millimil..DeLucia2006a g, 
       millimil..MPAHalo h
 where h.np between 2000 and 3000
   and h.snapnum=63
   and g.haloId = h.haloId
   and g.mag_b < 0
 group by 0*galaxyId, .2*(.5+floor(mag_b/.2))
union
select '200 - 300' as lim, 
       .2*(.5+floor(mag_b/.2)) as mag,
       count(*) as num
  from millimil..DeLucia2006a g, 
       millimil..MPAHalo h
 where h.np between 200 and 300
   and h.snapnum= 63
   and g.haloId = h.haloId
   and g.mag_b < 0
 group by 0*galaxyId+1, .2*(.5+floor(mag_b/.2))
order by lim,  mag  
"""
gal_lfs=cj.executeQuery(sql,"millimil")
In [116]:
groups=gal_lfs.groupby(['lim'])
f,(ax)=plt.subplots(1,1,figsize=(8,5))
for i,group in groups:
    ax.plot(group.mag,group.num,'-o',label=i)
ax.set_yscale('log');
ax.invert_xaxis()
ax.set_xlim(-14,-23)
ax.legend()
ax.set_xlabel("mag_b")
ax.set_ylabel("# gals in bins");

HG2¶

Find average galaxy properties as function of halo mass.

In [124]:
sql="""
select power(10.0, .1*(.5+floor(log(cast(g.np as real))/.1))) as halo_np,
       avg(g.stellarMass) as stars_avg,
       max(g.stellarMass) as stars_max,
       avg(g.bulgeMass) as bulge_avg,
       max(g.bulgeMass) as bulge_max,
       avg(g.mag_b-g.mag_v) as color_avg
  from millimil..DeLucia2006a g
 where g.snapnum= 63 
   and g.mag_b < 0
 group by floor(log(cast(g.np as real))/.1)
 order by 1
"""
gal_props=cj.executeQuery(sql,"millimil")
In [128]:
ax=gal_props.plot.scatter('halo_np','stars_avg',c='blue')
ax=gal_props.plot.scatter('halo_np','bulge_avg',ax=ax,c='red')
ax.set_xscale('log')
ax.set_yscale('log');
